<tr valign=top bgcolor="#CCCCCC">
<td align=center class="grey"><a name="2"></a><b>Map Notes</b></td>
</tr>
<tr valign=top>
<td>
<!--MAIN TABLES GO HERE-->
	<table border=0 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	<tr valign=top>
	<td class="bodycopy">
		<!--BODYCOPY BEGINS HERE-->

The Modern-up map is the same as for <a href=<PAGE>about_modern>Modern</a> with the following modifications.
<ol>
<li>
Addition of Ulster (Northern Ireland). Ulster is a canal province like Denmark or Istanbul, bordering Ireland, Liverpool and Clyde and separating the North-Atlantic Ocean from the Irish Sea.
<p><li>
The North- and South-Atlantic Ocean now touch each other, while Ireland borders the Mid-Atlantic Ocean.
<p><li>
(Trial version only) Addition of Central Sahara (Libya's desert area). Central Sahara is a landlocked province bordering Western Sahara, Libya, Eastern Sahara and Aswan. Aswan stretches eastwards towards the Libyan border.
<p><li>
(Trial version only) Addition of Slovenia. Slovenia is a non-sc country hemmed in between Austria, Hungary, Croatia and Venice. Slovenia has no coastline, so that Venice still borders Croatia.
</ol>

		<!--BODYCOPY ENDS HERE-->
	</td>
	</tr>
